  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: Geth/v1.8.10-stable-eae63c51/linux-amd64/go1.10.1\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nWhen debugging Mist integration with Augur, I discovered that light client geth sometimes will return \"0x\" rather than the correct answer.\r\n\r\nOn _Rinkeby_, with a light client, try the following curl:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{ \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"method\": \"eth_call\", \"params\": [{ \"from\": \"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\", \"to\": \"0x9bed8e86cfbe6959388fe886f01f7aa836047424\", \"data\": \"0xb80907f2\" }, \"latest\" ]}, function(a,b) { console.log(a,b) }' localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's been returning `{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0x\"}`. It _should_ be returning something along the lines of `0x509EFE80EAfdB9E143DeEB0cB0E00CF4f6cc1453` (encoded properly, of course).\r\n\r\nNow, before all y'all are all like \"But what if it's just a contract error?\", [this](https://github.com/AugurProject/augur-core/blob/2fc5b1dfc2339f88d4da07515b686d4c7a392a69/source/contracts/reporting/Universe.sol#L83-L85) is the code in question. Also, full geth nodes have been apparently working just fine, as the reputation token faucet on Rinkeby has been functioning for others. I can consistently get it to break with the light client.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time.",
